==English==

===Etymology===
From the comic feature "''The Yellow Kid''" in the ''Journal'' newspaper, first published in 1895.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|yellow press}} or '''yellow presses'''

# [[newspapers]] which publish [[sensationalist]] articles in favour of well researched and [[sober]] [[journalism]].

